## 8. Acceptance Criteria

### Functional

- [ ] Players can create a room and receive a unique 6-char room code
- [ ] Players can join a room using room code
- [ ] Room displays 2–4 players in real-time
- [ ] Host can start a round (if ≥2 players present)
- [ ] Round generates a random 4×4 letter board
- [ ] Timer counts down from 90 seconds, visible to all players
- [ ] Players can submit words via text input + GO button
- [ ] Invalid words show error message immediately
- [ ] Valid words are added to player's word list and score updates in real-time
- [ ] All players see the same global word count during round (`X unique / Y possible`)
- [ ] When timer reaches 0:00, round ends automatically
- [ ] Final rankings screen shows top 3 players with scores
- [ ] Answer key displays after round ends, grouped by word length
- [ ] Missed words section displays valid words not found by any player
- [ ] Host can press "NEW ROUND" to start a new round without leaving room
- [ ] WebSocket sync is real-time (< 200ms latency for submissions)

### Non-Functional

- [ ] Page loads in < 2 seconds (initial)
- [ ] Word validation response time < 100ms
- [ ] Board generation < 500ms
- [ ] Support 100+ concurrent rooms (cloud-based solution)
- [ ] Support 4 players per room, simultaneous submissions
- [ ] Mobile responsive (works on tablets, though not optimized for phones in MVP)
- [ ] No console errors or warnings (production build)
- [ ] Code organized into reusable components / modules

### UI/UX

- [ ] Button hover/focus states are clear
- [ ] Timer color changes (green → yellow → red)
- [ ] Input field clears on successful submission
- [ ] Visual feedback for valid/invalid words (checkmark, error message)
- [ ] Player list scrolls if > 4 players (edge case)
- [ ] Leaderboard is easy to read at a glance
- [ ] Answer key is searchable or scrollable
- [ ] No typos in UI text

