## 14. Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|------|------------|
| **Boggle** | Word game where players find words on a grid of letters within a time limit |
| **Board** | 4×4 grid of random letters |
| **Path** | Continuous sequence of adjacent cells (horizontal, vertical, diagonal) |
| **Deduplication** | Process of removing words submitted by multiple players |
| **Answer Key** | Complete list of all valid words possible on a given board |
| **Unique Word** | A word submitted by exactly 1 player in a round |
| **Room Code** | 6-character alphanumeric identifier for a game room (e.g., "ABC123") |
| **Round** | Single game session (90 seconds) on one board |
| **WebSocket** | Two-way communication protocol for real-time data sync |

